<item>
            <title>[LU-19586] project quota bug</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19586</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when&#160; setting project Id using lfs project -p &amp;lt;project_id&amp;gt; we started to get errors on the mds and oss in dmesg :&quot;LustreError: 168043:0:(lproc_quota.c:246:lprocfs_quota_seq_show()) babilon-OST0000-osd: failed to get rec: rc = -2&lt;br/&gt;
LustreError: 168050:0:(lproc_quota.c:246:lprocfs_quota_seq_show()) babilon-OST0000-osd: failed to get rec: rc = -2&quot; ,&quot;101591:0:(lproc_quota.c:246:lprocfs_quota_seq_show()) babilon-MDT0000-osd: failed to get rec: rc = -2&lt;br/&gt;
101591:0:(lproc_quota.c:246:lprocfs_quota_seq_show()) Skipped 1 previous similar message&lt;br/&gt;
101593:0:(lproc_quota.c:246:lprocfs_quota_seq_show()) babilon-MDT0000-osd: failed to get rec: rc = -2&lt;br/&gt;
101593:0:(lproc_quota.c:246:lprocfs_quota_seq_show()) Skipped 1 previous similar message&quot; it seems to be related to the file &quot;/proc/fs/lustre/osd-zfs/babilon-MDT0000/quota_slave/acct_project&quot; when we do cut to the file we see &quot;cat /proc/fs/lustre/osd-zfs/babilon-MDT0000/quota_slave/acct_project&lt;br/&gt;
prj_accounting:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;id: &#160; &#160; &#160;0&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; usage: &#160; { inodes: &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;363, kbytes: &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 7091 }&lt;br/&gt;
cat: /proc/fs/lustre/osd-zfs/babilon-MDT0000/quota_slave/acct_project: No such file or directory&quot; . this issue we have also tested the issue with alma 9.4 and lustre 2.16.1 and it seems to be fixed at tag v2.16.52 . the openzfs version we have tested are 2.2.7 and 2.2.8.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
